==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mule killer
<hw>Mule killer</hw>. <def>Any of several arthropods erroneously
supposed to kill live stock, in the southern United States, by stinging
or by being swallowed;</def> as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A whip
scorpion.</def> <mark>[Florida]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A walking-stick
insect.</def> <mark>[Texas]</mark> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A mantis.</def>
<sd>(d)</sd> <def>A wheel bug.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muleteer</ent>⟦br⟧
